text: im starting to believe in $btc again i know ive been off and on with it, sometimes very bullish, at times having my doubts ever since jerome powells speech on wednesday, ive lightened up to the idea of decentralized currency the federal reserve serves its purpose but has too much power in dictating the flow of the intermediate markets i believe if bitcoin was purchased more on main street, this free market would dictate true sentiment, a true reality of what people see in their daily lives and hence the real costs of money its about having an option with the usd as well and the way i see it is if crypto is strong, our usd will be too i have a few reasons why im a bit more bullish then before the speech the positive sentiment has a lot to do with a healthy free market that should define this digital currency in this growing global economy, i see bitcoin being like our usd, an intermediary from all fiat currencies i see a rising demand from all countries that have a limited and or struggling central banking system i do not think the usd will lose luster from all people, being it a stabled currency i believe having both stores of value prominent here in the united states will only give our economy emerging opportunities in technology and the growths of and this is just one reason why i believe should not pursue heavy taxation on business entities such as miners nor investors and people that already view cryptocurrencies as a store of value i feel that our public appointed officials in washington need to be lax in this space and let the market organically create more flexibility in the financial markets i also believe gary gensler of the sec should reconsider his approach to cryptocurrency and focus on his commitment to tame and cut corruption that exist such as naked short selling if he cannot get his priorities straight now like some argue, i believe its time for him to step down and move forward in his career even though i should be supportive, i think there has always been a thought for us that there is a better candidate for this very important position thank you for those that took a minute to read this tweet i just wanted to share my opinion once again and i feel like i will be sticking with this conclusion there is nothing wrong with bitcoin, the alternatives, and most of all ethereum im glad to be a bit more open minded than i was to this topic
